# PerformanceMonitor Integration Contract

Read `docs/PerformanceMonitor_Spec.md` for full spec.

## This System Is Built First
PerformanceMonitor exists before any other gameplay system. It provides the observability
layer that every subsequent system instruments into. If it doesn't exist yet, build it
before anything else.

## Usage Pattern
```gdscript
# Timing a block of work
PerformanceMonitor.begin("System.method_name")
# ... critical work ...
PerformanceMonitor.end("System.method_name")

# Reporting a count
PerformanceMonitor.set_count("System.metric_name", value)
```

## Canonical Metric Names — Use Exactly These
| Metric | Name |
|---|---|
| Dumb projectile update | `ProjectileManager.dumb_update` |
| Guided projectile update | `ProjectileManager.guided_update` |
| Projectile collision checks | `ProjectileManager.collision_checks` |
| AI state updates | `AIController.state_updates` |
| Physics move_and_slide | `Physics.move_and_slide` |
| Thruster allocation | `Physics.thruster_allocation` |
| Hit detection | `HitDetection.component_resolve` |
| Chunk load | `ChunkStreamer.load` |
| Chunk unload | `ChunkStreamer.unload` |
| Active projectiles | `ProjectileManager.active_count` |
| Active AI ships | `AIController.active_count` |
| Active physics bodies | `Physics.active_bodies` |
| Loaded chunks | `ChunkStreamer.loaded_chunks` |
| Content registry scan | `ContentRegistry.load` |

## Rules
- Only instrument operations expected to take > 0.1ms
- Never instrument inside inner loops — wrap the whole loop
- New systems MUST add their metrics to this table and to the spec
- The F3 debug overlay reads from PerformanceMonitor — keep the data clean
